org.hkijena.jipipe.api.nodes

Class JIPipeGraphNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hkijena.jipipe.api.nodes.JIPipeGraphNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JIPipeValidatable, JIPipeParameterCollection
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JIPipeAlgorithm, JIPipeProjectCompartment

    public abstract class JIPipeGraphNode
extends Object
implements JIPipeValidatable, JIPipeParameterCollection
    An algorithm is is a set of input and output data slots, and a run() function It is part of the JIPipeGraph.

    The workload of this node is considered optional (this means it can have an empty workload), which is important for structural graphs like the compartment or trait graph. Use JIPipeAlgorithm as base class to indicate a non-optional workload.

        public void setInfo(JIPipeNodeInfo info)
        Sets the JIPipeNodeInfo that describes this algorithm. Please note that this function can be very dangerous and break everything. This will affect how JIPipe (and especially the UI) handles this algorithm. A use case is to convert algorithms from internal representations to their public variants (e.g. JIPipeCompartmentOutput to IOInterfaceAlgorithm
